---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Slovakia Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/slovakia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Czech Republic for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/czech-republic' },
  { title: 'Austria for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/austria' },
  { title: 'Hungary for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/hungary' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'slovakiaFit', header: 'Slovakia Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€290-410/mo', slovakiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€340-480/mo', slovakiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€260-380/mo', slovakiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€245-360/mo', slovakiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Slovak Public', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: '14% income', slovakiaFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '€260-410', annual: '€3,120-4,920' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '€360-550', annual: '€4,320-6,600' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '€480-740', annual: '€5,760-8,880' },
  { category: 'Slovak Public Insurance', monthly: '14% of income', annual: 'Contribution-based' },
  { category: 'Slovak Private Clinic', monthly: '€30-80', annual: '€360-960' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Slovakia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Slovakia. Tatras mountains, Bratislava charm, affordable EU living, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Slovakia"
  subheadline="Slovakia offers dramatic Tatras mountains, historic charm, affordable EU living, and Eurozone membership—an underrated Central European retirement destination."
  heroImage="/images/countries/slovakia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Slovakia</h2>
  <p>
    Slovakia remains one of Europe's hidden gems—stunning High Tatras mountains, castles, cave systems, and affordable living. It's often overlooked for Czech Republic but offers similar appeal at lower prices. EU and Eurozone membership provides stability and easy travel.
  </p>

  <p>
    Bratislava offers capital-city living just 1 hour from Vienna with fraction of the cost. Košice is Slovakia's second city with good facilities. The Tatras region provides mountain living. Spa towns (Piešťany, Trenčianske Teplice) have therapeutic traditions.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good in cities; mix of public and private</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Slovak; German common; English in Bratislava</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €1,200-2,200/month; very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Continental; cold winters, warm summers</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Full EU member (Eurozone; uses EUR)</li>
      <li><strong>Vienna:</strong> Just 1 hour away for world-class healthcare</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Slovakia's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Slovakia has mandatory health insurance with three insurance companies (VšZP, Dôvera, Union). Quality is adequate—hospitals are functional if not cutting-edge. Bratislava has the best facilities. Private clinics are growing and offer faster service.
  </p>

  <p>
    Significant advantage: Vienna's world-class hospitals are just 1 hour from Bratislava. Many Bratislava residents use Vienna for complex care. Austrian healthcare is among Europe's best and accessible with appropriate insurance.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Vienna Proximity Advantage</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Bratislava is uniquely close to Vienna (65km)—closer than many Austrian cities. For serious medical needs, Vienna's AKH and other hospitals provide excellent care. Ensure your international insurance covers Austria. This proximity is a major healthcare advantage for Bratislava residents.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Slovakia offers EU-standard residence options:
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Residence (Financial Independence)</h3>
  <p>
    For those demonstrating sufficient income (typically €1,000+/month) and health insurance. Apply at Slovak embassy or locally. Valid up to 5 years. Can lead to permanent residence.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence for Property Owners</h3>
  <p>
    Owning property can support residence application when combined with proof of income and insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>EU/EEA Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement applies. Register with police after 90 days. Demonstrate sufficient resources and health coverage. Can join Slovak health insurance system once contributing.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Slovakia:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence application:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC initially; can join Slovak system</li>
    <li><strong>After residence:</strong> Can voluntarily join public insurance</li>
    <li><strong>Vienna access:</strong> Ensure coverage includes Austria</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Slovakia</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for residence applications. For Bratislava residents, ensure coverage includes Austria—Vienna hospitals are easily accessible. Slovak private clinics handle routine care affordably. Once eligible for Slovak public system, it provides adequate coverage for most needs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Slovakia, these providers offer good coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Slovakia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Covers Slovakia and Austria well</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive Central European pricing</li>
    <li><strong>Austrian access:</strong> Ensure Vienna coverage for best hospitals</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers that include both Slovakia and Austria.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Slovakia are among the EU's lowest:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Vienna nearby:</strong> Access world-class care without living there cost-wise</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Local care is cheap; high deductible works</li>
    <li><strong>Slovak public:</strong> Once eligible, 14% of income provides coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Private Slovak:</strong> Affordable clinics for routine needs</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Budget Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,800/month pension. Wants European base with Vienna access.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care covering Europe. Lives in Bratislava. Uses Vienna for complex care. Local clinics for routine.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€320/month. Lives well in Bratislava with Vienna healthcare backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Austrian EU Citizen, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Moving from Vienna to Bratislava for value. Austrian pension €1,600/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EU rights apply. Register in Slovakia. Keep Austrian coverage active for Vienna hospitals.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Slovak public + Cigna (for Austria complex care) ~€280/month. 60% savings vs Vienna living.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: British Tatras Lover, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, loves mountain hiking. Pension £1,700/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for comprehensive coverage. Lives near High Tatras. UK coverage for visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~€400/month. Mountain lifestyle at excellent value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does Slovakia compare to Czech Republic?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very similar culturally (languages mutually intelligible). Slovakia is cheaper (20-30% less). Czech Republic has slightly better healthcare infrastructure. Slovakia has Vienna proximity advantage. Prague is more cosmopolitan; Bratislava is smaller. Both offer excellent EU value.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I easily access Vienna healthcare?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—Bratislava to Vienna is 65km (1 hour). Regular trains and buses connect them. Vienna's hospitals are world-class. Ensure your insurance covers Austria. Many Bratislava residents routinely use Vienna for serious medical needs. It's a significant advantage of Bratislava location.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Slovak difficult to learn?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Slovak is Slavic—challenging for English speakers. Very similar to Czech (mutually intelligible). German is useful, especially older generation. English is growing, particularly in Bratislava and among younger Slovaks. Learning basics helps but you can manage with English in capital.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What are the spa towns like?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Slovakia has tradition of therapeutic spas (kúpele). Piešťany is famous for mud treatments. Trenčianske Teplice offers historic spa facilities. These provide legitimate therapeutic treatments for conditions like arthritis—often covered by Slovak public insurance. Quiet, healing environments popular with older visitors.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers covering both Slovakia and Vienna access.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Slovak authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
